Surface common Postgres integration and DBM setup issues through `datadog-agent diagnose`. The check now ships explicit pre-flight diagnostics covering connection/auth, Postgres version, `shared_preload_libraries`, `track_activity_query_size`, `track_io_timing`, `pg_stat_statements.max`, `pg_monitor` role, `pg_stat_activity` visibility, `datadog` schema, `pg_stat_statements` extension + readability, and the `datadog.explain_statement` function (probed against every database that query samples would target). DBM-specific probes are gated on the subfeature that consumes each dependency, and cascade-suppressed so a single root cause (SPL missing, `pg_monitor` missing, `datadog` schema missing) yields one actionable row instead of a chain of downstream FAILs. The statement collector now distinguishes `pg_stat_statements_not_loaded` (shared_preload_libraries missing) from `pg_stat_statements_not_created` (extension not installed) so `agent status` points at the right fix.
